        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 2 at 3:58PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 358 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of showers and
thunderstorms extending from near Bernalillo to Albuquerque and
Isleta Pueblo, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Albuquerque, Rio Rancho, Bernalillo, Corrales, Los Ranchos De
Albuquerque, Tijeras, North Valley, Paradise Hills, Rio Rancho
Intel Area and Cabezon.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 40 between Mile Markers 145 and 174.
Highway 550 between Mile Markers 1 and 9.
Interstate 25 between Mile Markers 211 and 249.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Blowing dust associated with thunderstorm winds can reduce
visibility below one quarter mile at times.</instruction>
